paragraphs.text:
/*Housing Prices Distribution*/

SELECT
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 10000 AND 99999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$10,000-$99,999`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 100000 AND 199999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$100K-$200K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 200000 AND 299999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$200K-$300K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 300000 AND 399999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$300K-$400K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 400000 AND 499999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$400K-$500K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 500000 AND 599999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$500K-$600K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 600000 AND 699999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$600K-$700K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 700000 AND 799999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$700K-$800K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 800000 AND 899999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$800K-$900K`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice BETWEEN 900000 AND 999999 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `$900K-$1M`,
  SUM(CASE WHEN SalesPrice>1000000 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `>$1M`
FROM housing

/* We get to know that more number of houses are in the range from $200K-$600K. */
